\par\par \b \uc2  Most bankers unwilling to predict  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 559 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Where are \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  headed in 1999? \par \par \uc2  A number of bankers interviewed on Thursday were reluctant to predict which way they are heading, citing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  about future political developments and a number of \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  trends in the country like the rupiah exchange rate and the rate of inflation. \par \par \uc2  Lulu Harsono, president of listed-Bank Pikko, said \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will depend chiefly on political developments in the country. \par \par \uc2  "The interest rate trend for 1999 will depend on the preparations for and the results of the June general election and other political events," Lulu said. \par \par \uc2  The rates will also move in line with changes in inflation. "Deposit rates should ideally be higher than the rate of inflation. If not, savings will simply be eaten up by inflation," he said. \par \par \uc2  Throughout 1998, depositors saw their savings falling behind, with inflation officially put at 77 percent for the entire year while \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  reached a peak of 60 percent. \par \par \uc2  Lulu said the government must fight to bring inflation down before \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  can be expected to fall from the present level of between 28 and 40 percent. \par \par \uc2  He questioned the government's projection that inflation would fall to 17 percent this year. \par \par \uc2  "This is so political," Lulu quipped. \par \par \uc2  He suggested that the government concentrate on stabilizing the prices of basic food items which have a strong influence over the consumer price index. \par \par \uc2  "The government's move to phase out fertilizer \b \highlight22\uc2 subsidies\b0 \highlight\uc2  is a mistake," he said. \par \par \uc2  Banking analyst I Nyoman Moena said \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's promissory notes (SBIs), as the benchmark interest rate, should stay at the current 35 percent level, considering Indonesia's still volatile political situation. \par \par \uc2  "The government has to be extra careful if it wants to bring the SBI rate lower than 35 percent, so as not to put pressure on the rupiah and thus induce inflation," he said. \par \par \uc2  Aulia Roza Putera, commissioner of rural bank BPR Sartaprindo in Jakarta, said that if the government could achieve the target of bringing inflation down to 17 percent, then \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could be kept in the range of 25 to 35 percent. \par \par \uc2  This again hinged on political developments in the first six months of this year, Aulia said. "Anything can happen," he added. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has vowed to continue cutting its benchmark rates in an effort to help the banking industry as well as the corporate sector in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  The current benchmark rate for one-month \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes (SBIs) is 35.06 percent, down 0.46 points from 35.52 percent last week and 70 percent in September, 1998. \par \par \uc2  State-owned Bank Rakyat Indonesia and publicly-listed Bank Negara Indonesia now both offer a 35 percent interest rate for one-month deposits, 32 percent for three months, 30 percent for a six-month period, and 28 percent for one year. \par \par \uc2  State-owned Bank Pembangunan Indonesia (Bapindo) offers rates of 40, 36, 31 and 29 percent for one month, three months, six months and one year respectively. \par \par \uc2  Bank Central Asia, Indonesia's largest private bank, offers rates of 39, 35, 31, and 28 percent for one month, three months, six months, and one year, respectively. \par \par \uc2  Bank NISP offers much lower rates, 33, 30, 26 and 26 for one month, three months, six months and one year. (02) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv18001ph\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
