\par\par \b \uc2  Troubled companies look to Miyazawa Plan for salvation. \b0\par\par\uc2 429 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The business sector here is hoping that aid disbursed under the auspices of the Miyazawa Plan will help to bail out firms facing the prospect of bankruptcy, according to a leading businessmen. \par \par \uc2  Fadel Muhammad, who is a director of the Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Kadin), said on Monday that over one thousand companies were in urgent need of fresh capital to stave of bankruptcy. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out that domestic banks would be unable to begin issuing fresh credit this year while going through a painful process of restructuring. \par \par \uc2  "If the Miyazawa Plan comes on stream we can save our national assets," he said after a meeting with Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance, and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar is scheduled to discuss the release of funds from the US$30 billion Miyazawa Plan during a meeting with Japanese officials scheduled for January 17. Japanese Finance Minister Kiichi Miyazawa proposed the plan last year as a means of assisting crisis-hit Southeast Asian nations. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian government hopes to secure $3 billion under the plan. \par \par \uc2  Fadel said that resuscitating the real sector was of equal importance to restructuring the troubled banking sector. \par \par \uc2  He urged the government to use aid from the Miyazawa Plan to temporarily take control of struggling companies and thereby prevent any further job losses. \par \par \uc2  "This may be against the privatization agenda, but it is very important to prevent more layoffs and widespread social unrest," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that the management of companies brought under government control should then be handed over to specially selected "capable businessmen." \par \par \uc2  He said that aid from the plan would help to meet the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which is expected to reach 4.8 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  He expressed confidence that current political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not prove a major obstacle to being granted the aid. \par \par \uc2  "Our political situation is still \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but I expect we will still be granted the aid. If not, our \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will get worse," he said. \par \par \uc2  In a recent announcement detailing the draft 1999/2000 state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the government said that foreign donors would provide $10.32 billion to meet the expected \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Most of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be met by the World Bank and the Asian Development Bank. The figure excludes aid from the Miyazawa Plan. \par \par \uc2  Analysts said that the Japanese aid would be crucial because of the strong possibility of \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  revenue targets falling short of their expected level as a result of the recession. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1c001ov\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
