\par\par \b \uc2  Bank recapitalization plan questioned. \b0\par\par\uc2 630 \uc2 words\par \uc2 13 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  urged the government on Tuesday to scale back the massive allotment in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the bank recapitalization program, and determine the institutions worthy of the assistance. \par \par \uc2  During a \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  hearing with finance minister Bambang Subianto, the ruling Golkar faction in the legislature complained the proposed Rp 18 trillion (US$2.4 billion) allotment was too burdensome on the 1999/2000 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The Golkar faction expects the recapitalization program to be selectively implemented and based on priorities," said Golkar spokesperson Ery Chajaridipura. \par \par \uc2  He believed priority should be on state banks, with assistance to private institutions earmarked for those which displayed prudent management. \par \par \uc2  President B.J. Habibie last week unveiled the draft \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in which the Rp 18 trillion would cover part of the coupon payment of the bonds to be issued by the government for the purpose of the bank recapitalization. \par \par \uc2  The total cost of the coupon payment will reach Rp 34 trillion, Rp 16 trillion of which will be financed through the sales of the banks' assets. \par \par \uc2  Golkar, while acknowledging that restructuring and recapitalizing the beleaguered banking sector were key for the recovery of the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , said the amount was too expensive and must be reduced. \par \par \uc2  The other three factions in the House also called on the government to cut back the allotted \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Why is the amount so large that it will cause too much burden on the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which in turn will also become a burden for the people who are already suffering?" said Indonesian Democratic Party spokesman Bambang Mintoko. \par \par \uc2  "Why should the faults of those living luxuriously become the responsibility of the people. This is very unfair and absurd." \par \par \uc2  The military faction also urged the government to set priorities in its bank recapitalization program because the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be concentrated on helping the poor to survive the 18-month-old \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  The Moslem-based United Development Party declared the "recapitalization \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is too large". \par \par \uc2  House members have been more outspoken in criticizing the government following the end of the Soeharto regime last year. \par \par \uc2  The government estimates the bank recapitalization will amount to at least Rp 300 trillion, in which it will provide 80 percent of the funding requirement through the issuance of the bonds. The remaining 20 percent will be provided by the banks. \par \par \uc2  Nearly 50 percent of the recapitalization cost will go to the state banks. \par \par \uc2  Banks eligible to join the program are those with a capital adequacy ratio (CAR) of between minus 25 percent and less than 4 percent. State banks will participate in the program although most have CAR of less than minus 25 percent. \par \par \uc2  The government is requiring all of the country's more than 200 commercial banks to have a minimum CAR level of 4 percent by the end of March this year or face likely closure. \par \par \uc2  CAR is the ratio between equity capital and risk-weighted assets. \par \par \uc2  The government has said that 61 banks are eligible to join the recapitalization program, 43 are ineligible unless they raise their CAR level, and 62 banks will be exempted because their CAR is more than 4 percent. \par \par \uc2  Analysts warn the recapitalization cost may become much larger if the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  fail to be realized, particularly amid the political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  before the June 7 general election. \par \par \uc2  The government projects zero \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, an inflation level of 17 percent and a rupiah-dollar exchange rate of Rp 7,500. \par \par \uc2  The House considered the assumptions "too optimistic" and said it would seek government explanations about its calculations. \par \par \uc2  Many also doubt whether the banks could come up with the 20 percent funding necessary, particularly in the current \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and social climate. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1d001qw\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
