\par\par \b \uc2  Govt to sell bonds worth billions of dollars to BI. \b0\par\par\uc2 526 \uc2 words\par \uc2 14 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The government plans to sell bonds worth tens of billions of dollars to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  to fund the bank recapitalization program, a senior minister said on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita told journalists after meeting President B.J. Habibie that fresh funds were needed "to improve the capital structure of the banking sector so that banks can improve their capital adequacy ratios." \par \par \uc2  "But the government will sell the bonds to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  and not to the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," Ginanjar added. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar's statement is supported by a \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  bill which the government presented to the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Wednesday. \par \par \uc2  The bill stipulates that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  is prohibited from directly buying debt instruments issued by the government, except those falling under the auspices of the bank recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  The announcement should end recent \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over how the government plans to finance the recapitalization of more then 70 domestic commercial banks through a program which has been costed at Rp 257.5 trillion (US$34.3 billion). \par \par \uc2  The government has said that it plans to provide up to 80 percent of the capital required by banks qualifying for the program. Bank owners will be required to provide the remaining 20 percent. \par \par \uc2  The total cost of interest payments due on the bonds in the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year is expected to be Rp 34 trillion. \par \par \uc2  The government has set aside Rp 18 trillion in the draft state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for 1999/2000 to cover part of this cost, while the remaining Rp 16 trillion is expected to come from the sale of assets belonging to banks taken under government control. \par \par \uc2  The period over which the bonds will mature has yet to be announced. \par \par \uc2  Most observers believe that the program will be nothing more than a "paper recapitalization". They expect the government to provide banks with "paper" bonds which can be sold to investors rather than inject fresh funds into the banks. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar's confirmation that the bonds will be sold to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  raises a question over where \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will get the funds required to purchase the bonds. The easiest way would be to print more money, a move which would result in high inflation. \par \par \uc2  But a Ministry of Finance official, who requested anonymity, said that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  would pay for the bonds in installments to avoid creating excessive inflationary pressures in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "\b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  will draw up a timetable which will govern when banks will be allowed to draw their money. That should reduce inflationary pressures," she said. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Finance Bambang Subianto said on Tuesday night that some of the money had already been channeled into the banking system through liquidity credits which had reached Rp 116.79 trillion as of Jan. 7. \par \par \uc2  Liquidity credits will be converted into government equity stakes in the banks which have received this assistance, provided that they qualify 