\par\par \b \uc2  Agriculture  \highlight22\uc2 budget \highlight\uc2  'too small'. \b0\par\par\uc2 729 \uc2 words\par \uc2 15 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The massive cut in the allotment for the agricultural sector in the 1999/2000 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  reflects the government's ignorance in identifying and taking advantage of the country's most promising sector, analysts have said. \par \par \uc2  They added the allotment was too small to encourage agricultural activities. \par \par \uc2  The executive director of the Center for Agricultural \b \highlight22\uc2 Policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  Studies, H.S Dillon, said on Wednesday that agriculture, as the only sector able to weather the crisis through recording positive growth, should have topped the list of the government's development agenda. \par \par \uc2  "The low \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  given to the agricultural sector shows an apparent indication that Habibie's government has failed to recognize, identify and take advantage of the country's most promising sector," he said during a discussion held by Indonesian Forum. \par \par \uc2  In the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft unveiled early this month by President B.J. Habibie, Rp 4.6 trillion (US$575 million) is allocated for agriculture. It is 40 percent lower than the Rp 7.4 trillion in the 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year ending in March. \par \par \uc2  About Rp 4.4 trillion of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is earmarked for the Ministry of Agriculture, with the remainder for the Ministry of Forestry and Plantations. \par \par \uc2  Dillon believed at least Rp 8.1 trillion should have been allocated. \par \par \uc2  Bungaran Saragih of the Bogor Institute of Agriculture said only agriculture recorded positive growth during the country's worst \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis in decades. \par \par \uc2  He said that during the 1997/1998 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, agribusiness recorded 2.2 percent growth as other sectors plunged into negative territory. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  draft clearly shows the government still puts its priority in the banking sector by allocating Rp 18 trillion for the bank recapitalization program, while neglecting other sectors which have greater potential to lift the country out of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis." \par \par \uc2  Dibyo Prabowo of the Center on Asia Pacific Studies at Yogyakarta's Gadjah Mada University said the tight \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  would render it even more difficult for farmers to enhance market infrastructure, provide better trade and processing services and enhance the quality of rural credit. \par \par \uc2  The three analysts said most of the government's policies in the agricultural sector remain counter-productive. \par \par \uc2  Bungaran said the government \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  on imposing a high export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on CPO resulted in a 70 percent drop in its export value last year. \par \par \uc2  He said the government would earn at least $2.5 billion from CPO exports in this year if it liberalized the trade. \par \par \uc2  The export value of CPO during 1998 only reached US$420 million, compared to $1.5 billion in the same period of 1997, he said. \par \par \uc2  "The government should promote the export of commodities which have the potential to be large foreign exchange earners to help the country out of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. The CPO industry falls into that category and any increase in exports would also be of benefit to smallholder farmers," Bungaran said. \par \par \uc2  Dibyo said government intervention to stabilize cooking oil prices had not only been ineffective, but had also caused trading in the commodity to become \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Inconsistency in government regulations covering trade in CPO and cooking oil will kill the business in the long term because the international market will come to view involvement with Indonesian palm oil producers as fraught with risk and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  Dibyo said that many international buyers have turned to Malaysia for CPO because dealing with the neighboring country posed less risk than if they buy the CPO from Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  He said the high export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  had discouraged CPO producers from exporting and caused the total supply of the commodity to flood the local market, especially after the rise in the rupiah's value to between Rp 7,500 and Rp 10,000 to the greenback in September. \par \par \uc2  "The export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  should be cut to reach as minimum as possible level," he said. \par \par \uc2  Dillon said the high export \b \highlight22\uc2 taxes\b0 \highlight\uc2  on CPO and its byproducts had halved the incomes of oil palm farmers as prices for the oil palm kernels had sharply dropped. \par \par \uc2  "The high export \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  has adversely affected the welfare of smallholder oil palm farmers and helped the urban consumers, those who are already rich," Dillon said. \par \par \uc2  The government currently impose a 60 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  on CPO. Earlier this month, it said the \b \highlight22\uc2 tax\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be slashed to 40 percent next month. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1f001v0\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\