\par\par \b \uc2  Analysts don't expect big hike in  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 683 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Experts expect the current increasing trend in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  aimed at providing support for the beleaguered rupiah will only be limited and temporary. \par \par \uc2  Senior banker I Nyoman Moena said on Saturday that the effectiveness of using monetary instruments to restrain the decline of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar would be minor because the main pressure for the currency was no longer \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors but concern over the country's political situation. \par \par \uc2  "Raising \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and market intervention will no longer be effective in influencing the rupiah's exchange rate because the pressure on the rupiah is not coming from \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  factors but from the people's perception that things will get worse as the general election approaches," he said. \par \par \uc2  "So the increase in \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  will be very limited," he added. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's benchmark one-month promissory note (SBI) interest rate rose to 35.89 percent in last week's auction. This is the second consecutive increase this month amid strong pressure on the rupiah, which dropped to a two-month low of Rp 9,200 to the dollar on January 13. \par \par \uc2  The local unit closed at Rp 8,925 to the dollar on Friday. \par \par \uc2  IMF Asia Pacific's director Hubert Neiss said on Friday that further increases in Indonesian \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could not be ruled out in the wake of the plunging rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The currency tumbled on various factors, particularly the contagion effect from the devaluation of Brazil's real, fresh riots in several parts of the country and expectation of students returning to the street this week. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah managed to hover at between Rp 7,500 and Rp 8,000 during the last couple of months of last year, which was a significant improvement on a more than Rp 15,000 in June and July. \par \par \uc2  The stabilizing currency had provided the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  with more room to allow the SBI interest rate to fall to 35 percent early this year, compared to more than 70 percent in August last year. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 's director Miranda Goeltom admitted on Friday that the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  had to tightened monetary conditions to minimize the volatility in the rupiah resulting from increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "But the increase in the SBI (\b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) is not so big. It's a very normal thing to happen in times when our currency is under pressure to provide a higher return on investment," she said. \par \par \uc2  She did stress, however, that domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  could fall to below 30 percent before the end of March as long as \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the political situation and the bank recapitalization plan can be minimized. \par \par \uc2  She said that it was not to the benefit of the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to impose a high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Pande Raja Silalahi, an economist at the Center for Strategic and International Studies, said the decision by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  to allow the SBI \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to move higher would only be a temporary measure to reduce the volatility in the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  "I think the monetary authority will remain with its commitment to continue reducing domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  He also agreed with Moena's view that if the pressure on the rupiah was coming from political worries and a lack of confidence in the current transitional government, employing a high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would not be effective in defending the battered currency. \par \par \uc2  "The confidence problem should be solved first," he said. \par \par \uc2  A "favorable" interest rate level is seen as a key to solving the country's battered real sector and banking industry. \par \par \uc2  The government started employing a tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  last year, as prescribed by the IMF, to curb inflation and stabilize the currency. \par \par \uc2  The high interest rate \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  received widespread criticism as it had dragged the country - and other IMF patients Thailand and South Korea - into a deeper recession. \par \par \uc2  The IMF last week admitted it had made some mistakes in handling the Asian crisis, but maintained that its tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  was the right prescription. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1p00297\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Jakarta stock exchange is expected to weaken. \b0\par\par\uc2 199 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 January 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Analysts said the index move on Jakarta stock exchange to a level lower than 400 was due to political crisis and inconducive global \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Jasso Winarto, executive director of