\par\par \b \uc2  Donor country support hinges on reform program. \b0\par\par\uc2 614 \uc2 words\par \uc2 26 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The international community will continue to provide financial support for Indonesia only if the government consistently implements its reform program within a framework of sound macroeconomic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) asserted on Monday. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank, which chairs the CGI, said in a statement that the group was calling for accelerated implementation of both the corporate and the financial restructuring programs to build up transparent and healthy institutions. \par \par \uc2  More than 80 representatives of the CGI donor countries and institutions met here on Monday to review the performance of the reform program in Indonesia and assess the impact of international assistance. \par \par \uc2  While the meeting was not called to discuss pledges of new aid, the group recognized the need for strong support from the donor community and international financial institutions. \par \par \uc2  "The basic message (of the meeting) is to support the people of Indonesia. But this comes with a caveat ... the reform programs must be implemented transparently and efficiently, not only in the social safety net program but also in other programs, including the banking and corporate reform programs," said World Bank Country Director for Indonesia Dennis de Tray at a press conference. \par \par \uc2  He explained that Indonesia would need US$9 billion in foreign assistance to finance its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year starting April, of which $4 billion in project financing has been secured. \par \par \uc2  The source for the remaining $5 billion, however, had not been secured, he added. \par \par \uc2  "We're still struggling for the $5 billion shortfall," said Chairman of the National Planning and Development Board (Bappenas) Boediono, who represented the government in the CGI meeting. \par \par \uc2  He said that the year 1999 would remain critical, not because of the threat of famine or severe inflation, but because of the potentially explosive social and political conditions, which he said would worsen if the right steps were not taken. \par \par \uc2  The government has expressed hopes that the $5 billion loans would primarily come from the World Bank, the Asian Development Bank, and Japan. \par \par \uc2  The Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry, Ginandjar Kartasasmita, last week visited Japan to try to secure $3 billion from the Miyazawa Plan assistance scheme. \par \par \uc2  The $30 billion Miyazawa Plan was announced last year by Japanese Finance Minister Siichi Miyazawa to help revive economically troubled Southeast Asian countries. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the government's reform program - designed together with the IMF - had re-emerged recently following \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  opposition to the costly banking recapitalization \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  proposed by President B.J. Habibie. \par \par \uc2  The total fund needed for the recapitalization is estimated at about one-third of gross domestic product, or approximately $35-40 billion. \par \par \uc2  The meeting also reviewed a World Bank study on the social impact of the crisis, which concluded that the effects have been less dramatic than were earlier estimated. \par \par \uc2  "People in urban areas are hurting more than those in the rural areas and people on Java appear to have borne more of the brunt of the crisis than those on other islands," said Lant Pritchett who summarized the findings of the study to the meeting. \par \par \uc2  The World Bank said the new data on poverty had important implications for \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  makers in designing and adjusting programs aimed at minimizing the effects of the crisis on the poor. \par \par \uc2  Boediono told the CGI meeting that the country's reform programs had worked well and, as a result, some positive signs had emerged, including declining inflation and a more stable currency. \par \par \uc2  "And there are signs that capital inflow has started to reappear as shown by the rising U.S. dollar deposits at local banks," he said.(rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1q001u0\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Prolonged instability - National companies change status to PMAs. \b0\par\par\uc2 531 \uc2 words\par \uc2 28 January 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  The investment body BKPM has said that the wave of status change from domestic investment firms (PMDN) and non-facility companies into foreign investment corporations (PMA) has intensified this year as a result of political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country and high \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  BKPM chief Hamzah Haz also said that many PMDN firms engaged in the domestic market-oriented commodity business currently face heavy financial problems as result of the prolonged monetary crisis. \par \par \uc2  Revenue earned by the companies, he added, does not match their financial obligations to creditors because of the sharp drop of the rupiah against the US dollar. \par \par \uc2  "The situation is exacerbated by the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  political situation here. The Karawang, Ambon, Kupang and other cases have made life difficult for PMDNs," he told Bisnis here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  As a result, said Hamzah, many PMDN firms as well as non-PMA/PMDN companies have transferred part or whole ownership to become PMA firms. \par \par \uc2  Such a development will continue so long as \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  here remain high. \par \par \uc2  Hamzah disclosed that PMDN firms that have changed their status into PMAs in November amounted to 20 companies with an investment of US$164,47 million. \par \par \uc2  Of that figure, 10 are PMDNs [with an investment of US$155,36 million], while the rest are non-facility firms. \par \par \uc2  He also said that PMDN firms that have shifted some or 100% of its shares to become PMA are a.o. PT Danaraksa Jakarta International Real Estate, PT Eternal Buana Chemical Industri, PT Jamafac, PT Unggul Equipment Sarana and PT Lion Super Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "It appears that most of them are in the industrial, real estate and retail sectors." \par \par \uc2  According to Bisnis data, PMDNs that have changed their status into PMA in the first semester of 1997 (the year the crisis set in) amounted to 36, while in the second semester the figure rose to 56 worth US$873,3 million. \par \par \uc2  In the period of January-March 1998 21 projects [worth US$1,859 billion] and in the period of 8 June-23 July 20 firms [worth Rp728 billion] changed their status, excluding PT Indofood Sukses Mandiri (ISM). \par \par \uc2  The BKPM chief said he found the status change move 'good' as a measure to maintain their activities and avoid layoffs (PHK). \par \par \uc2  Hamzah is optimistic that the change would help \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth. \par \par \uc2  "The share sale to foreigners is capital inflow and is not a loan. The position of local shareholders is on a par with their foreign counterparts although the former's stake may be smaller." \par \par \uc2  Noted businessman Djimanto shared Hamzah's view, saying "the share transfer move is a way to salvage companies." \par \par \uc2  He said another reason for it is to create a mother company overseas in order to set up a wider network. \par \par \uc2  Djimanto said that low domestic confidence has not only caused financial woes to PMDNs but also their ability to market their products overseas. \par \par \uc2  "The existence of a mother company could help them market their products in the international market," he said. \par \par \uc2  He disclosed that the in the past few months a number of footwear factories have transferred their shares to Hong Kong investors. (san). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv1s000yx\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
