\par\par \b \uc2  WB vows conditional support for Indonesia. \b0\par\par\uc2 508 \uc2 words\par \uc2 29 January 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The World Bank pledged on Thursday to help finance Indonesia's 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  estimated to reach 6 percent of gross domestic product. \par \par \uc2  World Bank vice president for East Asia and the Pacific region Jean-Michel Severino, however, said that its support would hinge on the country's consistent implementation of the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  reform program. \par \par \uc2  "We have a support plan for \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Indonesia, but this support as usual will be on condition of the progress of the reform ... this \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  and next \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year as well," he told reporters after meeting President B.J. Habibie together with the Bank's newly appointed country director for Indonesia Mark Baird and outgoing country director Dennis de Tray. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is expected to need a total of US$10 billion in foreign loans to finance its \b \highlight22\uc2 budget deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year starting April. \par \par \uc2  The government has said it already has $4 billion in project loans, while the remainder is yet to be secured. \par \par \uc2  The Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance, and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita has said that Japan, the World Bank, and the Asian Development Bank - traditionally Indonesia's major lenders - were expected to provide the further $5 billion needed in foreign loans. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar recently visited Tokyo to ask for part of the $30 billion Miyazawa aid program promised by Japan last year to help revive crisis-hit Southeast Asian nations. \par \par \uc2  The Consultative Group on Indonesia (CGI) said last week after a meeting here that Indonesia's major donor countries and institutions would continue to provide financial support only if the government consistently implements its reform program within a framework of sound macroeconomic \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the government's reform program - designed together with the International Monetary Fund - had reemerged recently following the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 ' opposition to the costly banking recapitalization plan proposed by President Habibie. \par \par \uc2  Severino said the meeting with Habibie mostly focussed on the bank's continuing support for the country's reform programs. \par \par \uc2  "We spend most of our discussions on the World Bank, which is supporting the reforms in Indonesia and helping in pushing ahead with the financial sector reform, the corporate restructuring and the social safety net, as well as the governments anticorruption \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said the bank was preparing a loan package to support the social safety net program, but that this needed further discussions with the government to improve the management, efficiency, and transparency of the program, which has been designed to help the poor in surviving the 18-month-old \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis. \par \par \uc2  The bank reported in the recent CGI meeting that the social effects of the crisis have been less dramatic than were earlier estimated. \par \par \uc2  "People in urban areas are hurting more than those in the rural areas and people on Java appear to have borne more of the brunt of the crisis than those on other islands," the bank said in its latest study on the social impact of the crisis. (rei/prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv1t0020u\par }\page {\par\fs20\b \uc2  Finance Minister - Govt ruling on funds for 12 banks not yet final. \b0\par\par\uc2 616 \uc2 words\par \uc2 30 January 1999\par \uc2 Bisnis Indonesia\par \uc2 BISNIS\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia\par \par \uc2  Finance Minister Bambang Subianto has asserted that the government ruling (PP) No. 4/1999 on the placement of government funds in 12 banks is not final yet and is presently being revised. \par \par \uc2  Bambang said here yesterday that the final figures for recapitalizing 10 regional government banks (BPD) and two private banks - Bank Lippo and Bank Sembada Artanugroho (Sanho)-still need to be discussed in detail with \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  (BI). \par \par \uc2  The PP No. 4/1999 of 18 January 1999 allows the government to place funds in 10 BPDs, Bank Lippo and Bank Sembada Artanugroho amounting to Rp4,29 trillion. \par \par \uc2  Of that amount, Lippo gets Rp3,753 trillion and Bank Sanho Rp18,46 billion. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  governor Syahril Sabirin said that the 12 banks will get the funds as they are 'most ready' among other banks that are also entitled to receive them. \par \par \uc2  "Lippo is most ready. In fact, they have paid up their capital [20% own capital with the remaining 80% government funds]," he said before, along with Bambang, meeting with President B.J. Habibie at Merdeka Palace here yesterday. \par \par \uc2  Bambang could not as yet say when PP No 4/1999 would be issued though Syahril Sabirin said that the figures are almost final. \par \par \uc2  He said that he hopes to see more PPs on the same subject issued up to March of this year. \par \par \uc2  "A PP can be issued for one bank and also a group of banks." \par \par \uc2  "Concerning BCA, I still need to talk to the finance minister. It's now already healthy. A program is already in place, what needs to be finalized is the size of government equity." \par \par \uc2  One banker said that government equity cannot as yet be placed before interest on the bonds is determined. \par \par \uc2  "Government equity in the bank will be swapped with government bonds." \par \par \uc2  He added that the finance minister must also determine whether it would retain voting rights or not. \par \par \uc2  "This has to do with the government's rights over the bank for up to three years, at which time the bank's owners still have the right to buy back the government's stake in the bank." \par \par \uc2  Another Bisnis source said the delay of the program concerning the 12 banks was caused by the IMF's rejection of it, as 80% of the recapitalization funds coming from the government must be met by 20% from the owners' side. \par \par \uc2  "It is as if the bank [Lippo] does not pay up in cash," he said. \par \par \uc2  The source said that the total amount of funds needed by Lippo is about Rp4,57 trillion, Rp1 trillion of which will have to come from Lippo. \par \par \uc2  Roy E. Tirtadji, a commissioner of Bank Lippo, said that funds supplied by the owner [Mochtar Rijadi] is in the form of cash derived from the sale of Bank Lippo in California and a house owned by James T. Ryadi in the US. \par \par \uc2  "Funds paid up account for 20% of the recapitalization need may not come from loans in whatever form. This will be checked by BI and controlled during a due diligence conducted by an international auditor," he told Bisnis last night. \par \par \uc2  Roy said Bank Lippo was chosen in the first batch of banks because the bank's owner had early on remitted Rp1 trillion in cash. \par \par \uc2  Other banks may have no cash money and may still be waiting for the political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions to become less \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2 , he said. \par \par \uc2  "Mochtar Rijadi should actually be praised because of his courage to invest under \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertain\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions, and should not be suspected of anything at all," he added. (17/dj/gps/ass). \par \par \uc2  (c) 1999 Bisnis Indonesia. \par \par \uc2 Document bisnis0020010901dv1u000zb\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
