\par\par \b \uc2  Stock prices predicted to remain under pressure. \b0\par\par\uc2 569 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 February 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  11 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Share prices in the local stock market are expected to remain under pressure again this week with most investors keeping watch on the development of the country's political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  situation, financial analysts said. \par \par \uc2  They said lack of positive leads from the domestic market, coupled with ever-present fears of a deepening global financial crisis would further weigh down market sentiment in the local stock market. \par \par \uc2  Anton Karlam, head of research at Panin Sekuritas, said possible high inflation for January and signs of increasing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would heavily pressure the local bourse. \par \par \uc2  "Moreover, \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over our banking recapitalization program would languish the already gloomy outlook of our market," he said. \par \par \uc2  He noted that \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  outcry over the government's plan to provide Rp 3.75 trillion (US$415 million) to help recapitalize Lippo Bank, controlled by Mochtar Ryadi, would cast a shadow on the market. \par \par \uc2  Moreover, the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  has balked at the government's proposal to set aside Rp 16 trillion in the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  to pay the interests of bonds used to recapitalize troubled banks. \par \par \uc2  Securities analysts said that the ups and downs of other equity markets in the region would continue to dictate the movement of the local market. \par \par \uc2  "I think the market will be directionless this week, with a tendency to weaken a bit, led by the movement in the regional market," one analyst with a joint venture securities house said. \par \par \uc2  Panin's Anton said that investors, especially foreigners, would not be tempted to reenter the local battered market as they could not find any meaningful guide to invest here. \par \par \uc2  "Foreign investors have not been satisfied with developments on Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and political fronts," Anton contended. \par \par \uc2  Stockbrokers said persistent market fear that antigovernment protest to take place in the capital and other major cities would further affect the market. \par \par \uc2  "Though sentiment remains bleak, we expect domestic investors to enter the market again," Vonny Juwono, institutional sales broker with Trimegah Securindolestari, said. \par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Stock Exchange (JSX) main composite index rose 2.3 percent, or 9.51 points, to 411.93 last week compared to 402.40 the previous week. \par \par \uc2  Daily average volume fell to 250 million shares changing hands last week compared to 279.5 million shares the previous week, while daily average transaction fell to Rp 267.88 billion from Rp 416.87 billion. \par \par \uc2  Like the stock prices, currency dealers and financial analysts said that sentiment on the rupiah would remain bearish in the coming weeks despite repeated assurances by the monetary authority that it would defend the rupiah whenever there was strong speculative attack by offshore operators. \par \par \uc2  A chief dealer with a joint venture bank said the rupiah would not recover significantly until the general election in June. \par \par \uc2  Although the rupiah managed to rise below the 9,000 level last weekend, it did not indicate any improvement in the sentiment on the rupiah, he said. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed at 9,050 on Friday last week after hitting an intraday high at 8,800. \par \par \uc2  He warned, however, that renewed attacks on the rupiah could happen anytime, especially when social tensions run high. \par \par \uc2  "Some offshore operators are still watching closely as to when to attack the rupiah," the dealer said. \par \par \uc2  Nevertheless, he predicted that the rupiah would trade between 9,000 and 9,400 this week. (aly) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv210026t\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
