ednesday as saying that the delay in Japan's decision on Indonesia's share of the Miyazawa funds could be caused by the large amount of funds requested by the government. \par \par \uc2  Out of the aid plan, Thailand would get about $1.8 billion, Malaysia would receive $1.5 billion, the Philippines would get $1.4 billion, while Indonesia had asked for $5 billion, he said. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar also said on Wednesday that Indonesia's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery was still hampered by political and security \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The political processes in Thailand and South Korea have successfully been completed. However, we are just now going through the process," he said. \par \par \uc2  "Many people are still waiting for the results of the general election," he said, referring to the election to be held on June 7. (das) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv24002es\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
