\par\par \b \uc2  BI not budging from high  \highlight22\uc2 interest rates \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 425 \uc2 words\par \uc2 12 February 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  12 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said on Thursday the tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would remain in place as \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  continued to put pressure on the rupiah and prodded inflation in the run-up to the June general election. \par \par \uc2  He believed the country's social and political condition, combined with the faring of the bank recapitalization program, would exert strong influence on progression of the monetary condition. \par \par \uc2  External developments, including \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  occurrences in Latin America, China and Japan, would also affect the rupiah's movement. \par \par \uc2  "That is why we will continue adopting a cautious \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  so as not to create volatility which can disrupt monetary stability, both on inflation and the rupiah," he told \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  Commission VIII for state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance at a hearing on the bank recapitalization program and monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said the tight monetary \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would be relaxed immediately after the rupiah regained its strength and pressure on inflation subsided. \par \par \uc2  "This is only a temporary measure. I'm optimistic that the rupiah will strengthen, which will provide more room for a lower interest rate." \par \par \uc2  The interest rate on one-month \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  promissory notes rose from 36.97 percent to 37.15 percent at the Wednesday weekly auction. \par \par \uc2  It was the fifth consecutive increase in the benchmark rate. The rate was on a downward trend in the final quarter of 1998, from more than 70 percent in September to 35 percent in December, in accordance with the rupiah strengthening from a record low of Rp 17,000 to the U.S. dollar to around Rp 7,500 late last year. \par \par \uc2  The currency lost its footing in January, exceeding the Rp 9,000 level, following the devaluation of the Brazilian currency and poor political developments at home, as well as the \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  uproar over the government bank recapitalization program. \par \par \uc2  Inflation in January also surged to 2.97 percent, deviating from the downward trend during the final months of 1998. \par \par \uc2  Worries over the country's political situation heightened following recent outbreaks of rioting and unrest in several parts of the nation. \par \par \uc2  Many are questioning whether the country can have a peaceful political transition through the June 7 general election, heralded as the first open and democratic poll after more than 30 years of the authoritarian presidency of Soeharto, especially as the full impact of the 18-month-old \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis will be felt this year. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah closed steady at Rp 8,700 to the dollar on Thursday. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv2c002ph\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
