\par\par \b \uc2  House approves revised State  \highlight22\uc2 Budget \highlight\uc2 . \b0\par\par\uc2 389 \uc2 words\par \uc2 27 February 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Friday approved the 1999/2000 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  with some changes in revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  targets, despite warnings by some analysts that the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  is too optimistic. \par \par \uc2  Following revisions, the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the 1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, which begins in April, is a balanced Rp 219.6 trillion (US$25.8 billion), higher than the Rp 218.2 trillion initially proposed by the government. \par \par \uc2  "The 1999/2000 State \b \highlight22\uc2 Budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been carefully and realistically designed based on assumptions and evaluations of various internal and external developments, both current and future," finance minister Bambang Subianto told the parliament in a speech. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumes zero \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth, from an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  contraction of more than minus 13 percent last year. Inflation is assumed at 17 percent, down from 66 percent the previous year, while the exchange rate for the rupiah against the U.S. dollar is forecast at Rp 7,500, up from Rp 10,600. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, have said that the assumptions are too optimistic, particularly in view of the probable chaotic situation ahead of the June 7 general election and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  over the bank recapitalization program and corporate overseas debt restructuring. \par \par \uc2  A failure to achieve the macroeconomic assumptions would affect the revenue and \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  sides of the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , according to analysts. \par \par \uc2  The government and the House engaged in an intense debate over the \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2 , first brought before the House in January, resulting in various revisions. \par \par \uc2  Intense \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  debates and revisions are phenomenons which were never seen during the 32-year reign of former autocratic president Soeharto. During Soeharto's New Order regime, the House merely rubber-stamped the annual \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  after a few weeks of perfunctory debates. \par \par \uc2  The revisions in the state \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  include a 15 percent to 50 percent salary increase for civil servants. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the bank recapitalization program has been lowered to Rp 17 trillion from the initially proposed Rp 18 trillion. Another Rp 500 billion in expenditures have also been slashed. \par \par \uc2  The government also revised its revenue target from the excise duty on cigarettes, raising it by Rp 800 billion to Rp 10.16 trillion. The estimated nontax revenue target - mainly dividends from state-owned companies - has also been increased by Rp 700 billion to Rp 26.49 trillion. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv2r002vv\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
