\par\par \b \uc2  People's  \highlight22\uc2 economy \highlight\uc2  concept worries U.S. investors. \b0\par\par\uc2 647 \uc2 words\par \uc2 25 March 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The populist \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  approach adopted by the President B.J. Habibie administration has U.S. investors worried. \par \par \uc2  The president of the American Chamber of Commerce in Indonesia (Amcham Indonesia), James W Castle, said here on Wednesday that many American businesspeople feared that Indonesia's people-oriented \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could turn into a socialist \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "Many reports on the government's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  have created fear among foreign businesses," he said. "The thing they most fear is that if the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  turns out to be a socialist \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the granting of resources is merely a task rather than an effort to promote a competitive market," he said at a business luncheon hosted by the chamber. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Cooperatives and Small Enterprises Adi Sasono, a staunch promoter of Indonesia's people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , however, said that such fears were groundless. \par \par \uc2  In a speech at the luncheon he said that many people had the wrong perception about the government's increased attention on the development of small and medium-scale businesses. \par \par \uc2  Speaking to reporters after the lunch, Castle said that if the government turned the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic policy\b0 \highlight\uc2 's direction to socialism, it would mean there would be no respect for private property. \par \par \uc2  "Businesspeople fear that there will be a lack of respect for private properties," he added. \par \par \uc2  He said socialism had failed in many countries, and if it came about in Indonesia, American investors would have reason to fear. \par \par \uc2  "So American investors want clarification of minister Adi's programs, especially on those related to the people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  concept and empowering small and medium enterprises and cooperatives". \par \par \uc2  Castle said that many European countries adopted an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  system similar to a socialist \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , but those countries respected private property and had a good judicial system, in which all legal disputes could be solved. \par \par \uc2  "There is concern over the judicial system in Indonesia," he said. \par \par \uc2  Adi said the people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  concept adopted by the Indonesian government had nothing to do with socialism. \par \par \uc2  "A people-oriented \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  is very different from a socialist \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We will not protect small businesses by creating barriers for big businesses entering the market. \par \par \uc2  "The government will instead try to create a balance where small enterprises grow rapidly and big companies continue to do business as usual," he said. \par \par \uc2  A balanced situation will only emerge if the rules of the game are upheld and opportunities are available for all, especially small and medium enterprises and cooperatives. \par \par \uc2  He said large business groups had the wrong perception about the people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and they feared that the concept would mean the government could transfer their assets to small businesses. \par \par \uc2  "There are misperceptions by some people that the government will take over the assets of troubled conglomerates and distribute them among small businesses. Our program has nothing to do with that at all, it is all a misunderstanding," he said. \par \par \uc2  Adi's people-oriented \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  concept has received mixed reactions both from domestic and foreign observers. Concerns have been raised that the \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could involve the forced redistribution of assets belonging to large, troubled companies and banks to small businesses. \par \par \uc2  Castle said that basically, American investors did not have a problem with the implementation of a people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  in Indonesia. \par \par \uc2  "As a matter of fact, the United States is the best example of how the people's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  works," he said. \par \par \uc2  "The explanation given by minister Adi is very encouraging, and I think we 99 percent agree on what he said. I hope American businesspeople have a clearer view after hearing his explanation," he added. \par \par \uc2  Castle said that mining and natural resource-based businesses remained attractive to American investors amid Indonesia's prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  crisis, but many investors preferred to wait and see due to \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the country's political and social climate. (gis) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv3p00b02\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
