\par\par \b \uc2  S&P flip-flops on RI foreign currency rating downgrade. \b0\par\par\uc2 588 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 April 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  9 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): U.S. rating agency Standard and Poor's hurriedly restored Indonesia's long-term foreign currency rating on Wednesday, just one day after its downgrade was protested by the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  It announced it "reset" the rating from "Selective Default" (SD) to "Triple-C-Plus". \par \par \uc2  "The restitution of the long-term foreign currency issuer credit rating to 'Triple-C-Plus' from 'SD', one day after Standard and Poor's downgrade to 'SD', reflects Indonesia closure of a distressed rescheduling of US$210 million of principal on the rated $350 million syndicated loan," it said. \par \par \uc2  On Tuesday, the agency said the rescheduling of the $310 million loan disbursed in 1994 by a syndicate of 70 banks, now led by Japan's Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Ltd, qualified it for the selective default rating. \par \par \uc2  On Wednesday, however, it said that all 70 of the affected creditor banks "have, via powers of attorney, signed the rescheduling amendment, which now supersedes the original indenture and is enshrined in law. \par \par \uc2  "Therefore Indonesia's sovereign default is cured, removing an obstacle to the rescheduling of $4.2 billion of principal-repayment obligations to Paris Club bilateral creditors due between August 6, 1998, and March 31, 2001". \par \par \uc2  In protesting the downgrade, \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  said late Tuesday the government had never defaulted on its commercial bank loans or bonds. \par \par \uc2  BI director Dono Iskandar Djojosubroto said the country remained current on all interest payments on its obligations and was fully committed to staying current on all commercial debt, including its $400 million Yankee bond maturing in 2006, and its $300 million floating rate notes maturing in 2001. \par \par \uc2  The selective default rating applies when a country has selectively defaulted on an issue or class of obligations, but will continue to make timely payments on its other obligations. \par \par \uc2  The Triple-C rating denotes a situation in which a country is "currently vulnerable to nonpayment" and is dependent on \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions to repay debt. \par \par \uc2  Standard and Poor's reaffirmed on Wednesday Indonesia's "B" long-term local currency issuer credit rating and assigned "C" short-term foreign and local currency credit ratings to Indonesia. "The outlook is now stable." \par \par \uc2  The agency said the ratings and stable outlook reflected the restoration of monetary discipline, the stabilization of the near-term international liquidity position and ongoing efforts to restructure and recapitalize the banking system. \par \par \uc2  But the ratings are constrained by a devastated corporate sector, which owes about $62 billion to foreign creditors, and ongoing political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The planned four-month period between parliamentary and presidential elections later this year augurs a \b \highlight22\uc2 policy\b0 \highlight\uc2  hiatus, and could be followed by a new administration with a weaker commitment to honoring sovereign debt obligation. \par \par \uc2  "Moreover, prolonged \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  stresses could prompt a new government to seek additional Paris Club bilateral debt rescheduling, an initiative that could trigger defaults on rated debt under burden sharing stipulations. \par \par \uc2  Standard and Poor's said actions on Indonesia's sovereign foreign currency rating did not impact its ratings on the country's corporate issuers. \par \par \uc2  "Ratings of all Indonesian corporates remain on CreditWatch with negative implications." \par \par \uc2  According to Standard and Poor's, CreditWatch highlights an emerging situation which could materially affect the profile of a rated corporation and can be designated as positive, developing or negative. \par \par \uc2  The agency said it would continue to "closely monitor the credit impact of the crisis, and will update ratings as business and financial events affecting credit quality emerge". (rid) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv41007mz\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
