\par\par \b \uc2  Indosat lanches expansion of non-core business projects. \b0\par\par\uc2 421 \uc2 words\par \uc2 1 May 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Despite the country's political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 , publicly listed international telecommunications firm PT Indosat launched on Friday its fourth non-core business project in two months. \par \par \uc2  Indosat president Tjahjono Soerjodibroto said the firm's \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  for non-core business activities had not been affected by the turbulence in the country. \par \par \uc2  "It's business as usual for us," he told The Jakarta Post on the sidelines of the launching of an Indosat TV program. The launching was also attended by Minister of Education and Culture Juwono Sudarsono. \par \par \uc2  The TV program, called Indosat Galileo, will present a popular scientific quiz to be aired by the private Surya Citra TV station every Sunday starting on May 2. \par \par \uc2  The name of the program was taken from the Italian astronomer and physicist who invented the telescope in 1609. \par \par \uc2  Tjahjono said the \b \highlight22\uc2 spending\b0 \highlight\uc2  was not a direct profit-oriented investment. \par \par \uc2  "We want to build an image of Indosat as a firm which cares about education, science and technology," he said. \par \par \uc2  He said that it was not a measure to counter the increasingly popular music TV program and adventure TV serial launched by PT Satelindo, Indosat's only competitor. \par \par \uc2  Indosat has launched several cooperation agreements over the past two months. \par \par \uc2  The company agreed on Wednesday with Bank Bali and PT Jatis Enterprise Integration Consulting to develop an Internet-based shopping service. \par \par \uc2  Last month, Indosat also agreed with retailer PT Matahari Putra Prima and local cosmetics maker Martha Tilaar to engage in an electronics venture. \par \par \uc2  Indosat was one of the state companies initially to be included in the government privatization program in the 1998/1999 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, but was later postponed to the current \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year partly due to a regulations snag. \par \par \uc2  Tjahjono said the bidding process for Indosat would start after the new telecommunications bill is approved by the \b \highlight22\uc2 House of Representatives\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  Reports said earlier that three international telecommunications giants, including Australia's Telstra and French Telecom, have shown interest to take up the government stake in Indosat. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia's general election scheduled for June 7 is expected to be the country's first open and democratic election after more than 32 years under the authoritarian rule of former president Soeharto. Many people fear increasing bloody unrest in the run-up to the election, which could prompt a massive exodus. \par \par \uc2  Analysts, however, said Indosat would enjoy a big increase in incoming calls if a great amount of people do leave the country. \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv510087b\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
