\par\par \b \uc2  Government cautioned on signs of  \highlight22\uc2 economic \highlight\uc2  recovery. \b0\par\par\uc2 805 \uc2 words\par \uc2 10 May 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Experts have warned the government not to overreact to early signs of an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery, as a fundamental \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  turnaround was yet to arrive. \par \par \uc2  Senior banker I Nyoman Moena said at the weekend that excessive optimism might lead to a misjudgment of the real situation and lead to the development of incorrect policies. \par \par \uc2  "We must be extra careful in reading the (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) indicators. The fundamentals (for a sustainable recovery) are not there yet," he told The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2  Moena called on the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  not to be too hasty in allowing domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to drop, as the rupiah was still volatile and an inflationary threat remained. \par \par \uc2  "There is still a big question mark over the (\b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2 ) developments. If \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  plummet we may get trapped. A rush on the banks may happen again," the former \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  director said. \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) announced last week that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  grew by 1.34 percent in the first quarter of 1999, from the fourth quarter of last year. It also reported that inflation in April was negative at 0.68 percent, better than the negative inflation of 0.18 percent in March. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah continued to stabilize at Rp 8,000 per U.S. dollar, despite the declining trend in domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . A few months ago, the local currency was hovering between Rp 8,600 to Rp 8,900. \par \par \uc2  The stock market has been bullish for the past few weeks, driven by an inflow of foreign funds. \par \par \uc2  The encouraging developments have prompted government officials to express optimism the country will achieve \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery earlier than expected. \par \par \uc2  Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita said the government was considering a revision of its \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  growth projection in the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year to between 0 percent to 2 percent, from earlier estimates of zero growth. \par \par \uc2  He forecast that inflation would be around 10 percent, compared to an initial prediction of 17 percent. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar expected domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to drop below 30 percent before the end of the month, while \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin projected \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  would fall to between 20 percent and 25 percent before the end of the year. \par \par \uc2  The interest rate for the benchmark \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory note is currently at slightly above 31 percent. \par \par \uc2  Pande Radja Silalahi, an economist at the Centre for Strategic and International Studies, said the government was overreacting by revising \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  assumptions amid the persisting \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  He said the fate of the government bank restructuring program, along with efforts to restructure the banks' non-performing loans (NPLs) had yet to be resolved. \par \par \uc2  "The government is overly optimistic. There's no guarantee for the two programs to work as planned." \par \par \uc2  Pande said a slowdown in the programs could be detrimental for confidence building, a key element for a sustainable \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  The government has closed down many ailing banks and plans to recapitalize nine private banks, take over 11 private banks, seven state banks and 12 provincial development banks, at a total cost of some Rp 500 trillion (about US$62.5 billion). \par \par \uc2  But the success of the recapitalization program would also depend on the restructuring of the banks' NPLs. \par \par \uc2  The government plans to start the restructuring of the NPLs with the 20 largest debtors of state banks. \par \par \uc2  The government delayed the initial April 30 restructuring deal, which was rescheduled for agreement with the 20 debtors in late August. Many believed that the postponement of the plan was the result of pressure from well-connected debtors. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency (IBRA) has assumed over Rp 100 trillion in NPLs from the seven state banks, of which approximately Rp 60 trillion is believed to be owed by the 20 largest debtors. \par \par \uc2  IBRA has also surrendered to pressure to return some of the NPLs to the state banks. IBRA deputy chairman Eko S. Budianto said on Friday the agency would hand over the management of individual NPLs of less than Rp 25 billion back to the state banks. \par \par \uc2  Pande also said the April negative inflation was not a sign of a deflationary trend to justify the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's plans to lower \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "The negative inflation was primarily caused by the declining purchasing ability of people," he said. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia suffered more than a 13 percent \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  contraction in 1998, causing millions to lose their jobs. The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  continued to contract by more than 10 percent in the first quarter of 1999, compared to the same period last year. \par \par \uc2  "The \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will remain under strong pressure in 1999," said BPS chief Suwito Sugito. \par \par \uc2  He forecast the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would contract by 1.02 percent in 1999, assuming that the upcoming June general election was nonviolent and credible. (rei) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv5a008u1\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
