\par\par \b \uc2  LETTER - Taiwan opposes arms race. \b0\par\par\uc2 553 \uc2 words\par \uc2 11 May 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  4 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  In response to the article entitled "China lashes U.S. over weapon sales to Taiwan" in The Jakarta Post on May 7, 1999, I would like to express Taipei's point of view. \par \par \uc2  In March 1996, Beijing lobbed missiles at Taiwan. Since then, the People's Liberation Army has deployed more than 100 of its newest M-9 and M-11 missiles across the Taiwan Straits, and the number may reach 650 by 2005, according to Pentagon. \par \par \uc2  In August 1998, North Korea launched missiles over Japan. These incidents and security threats from elsewhere prompted the U.S. to more than double its ballistic-missile-defense \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  in February 1999 to a record US$10 billion between now and 2005. A part of the program is the Theater Missile Defense (TMD), designed to neutralize ballistic missile attacks in North East Asia. \par \par \uc2  Will the Republic of China participate in the development and employment of TMD? Our views follow. \par \par \uc2  We promote regional stability and prosperity, and oppose the arms race. Our \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  development has garnered the accolade of the "Taiwan miracle", and is a major source of our people's much enhanced wellbeing. To ensure our continued prosperity, we must actively promote regional stability and fully support any effort toward it. To engage in an arms race, siphons off the life-blood of one's \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We oppose the arms race, as it is incompatible with our national interest. \par \par \uc2  Beijing's militant behavior is threatening regional stability. Beijing has not renounced the use of force against Taiwan, which Beijing has from time to time reiterated. The Beijing military buildup substantiates its militant rhetoric. Since 1989, its official defense \b \highlight22\uc2 budget\b0 \highlight\uc2  - not to mention the actual \b \highlight22\uc2 expenditure\b0 \highlight\uc2  - has grown at a double digit rate, far outstripping the inflation rate. \par \par \uc2  Our self-defense, like our survival, is an inalienable right commonly shared by all nations. TMD, by definition, is a system of defense, not offense. The Republic of China is an independent and sovereign country. We reserve the right to decide whether to participate in the TMD. Beijing's opposition on this matter merely belies its intent of aggression. \par \par \uc2  The proliferation of weapons of massive destruction into the hands of irresponsible states poses a threat to not only regional but also global peace and stability. Against this threat, TMD may offer some prospects of deterrence and defense. However, we fully realize the evolving nature of the TMD technology, the sizable financial commitment involved, and the strategic \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2  of cross-strait relations. We are seriously concerned with the issue and are cautiously assessing it before making a decision thereon. There are many factors influencing our assessment. But Beijing's behavior as such, or possible reduction thereof in the future, will ultimately determine whether we decide to participate in the TMD. \par \par \uc2  As the world enters the 21st century, the sweeping waves of democracy can no longer be held back. While we have chosen the right side of history, Beijing has not. We hope Beijing will soon. Between democracies, few wars have occurred in this century, and none since the end of World War II. In the long run, only if Mainland China democratizes can regional stability and prosperity be assured. \par \par \uc2  CINDY CHIEN \par \par \uc2  Assistant \par \par \uc2  Information Division \par \par \uc2  Taipei \b \highlight22\uc2 Economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  and Trade Office \par \par \uc2  Jakarta \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv5b008qe\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
