\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah expected to strengthen soon. \b0\par\par\uc2 697 \uc2 words\par \uc2 3 June 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): Coordinating Minister for \b \highlight22\uc2 Economy\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita predicted on Wednesday that the rupiah would get stronger after next week's general election. \par \par \uc2  He said that both the local currency and the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  would further gain strength with progress in the bank recapitalization program and corporate debt restructuring. \par \par \uc2  "After the election, with political certainty, I think it (the rupiah) will strengthen," he told reporters ahead of a cabinet meeting. \par \par \uc2  "God willing, the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  will recover by itself if all the \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  programs including bank recapitalization and corporate debt restructuring are implemented," he added. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is set to hold its first multiparty general election on June 7 after more than 30 years under the authoritarian rule of former president Soeharto. \par \par \uc2  The election campaigning activities which started on May 19 will end on Friday. The campaigning has so far been relatively non-violent despite the bloody rioting that took place in several parts of the country. \par \par \uc2  But the rupiah closed slightly lower at Rp 8,150 on Wednesday against the U.S. dollar from Tuesday's close of Rp 8,100 amid fears of possible violence in the final days of the election campaign. \par \par \uc2  The Indonesia Democratic Party of Struggle (PDI Perjuangan) is set to hold its final campaign today in Jakarta and its massive number of supporters are expected to parade all through the main streets of Jakarta, causing long traffic jams. \par \par \uc2  The ruling Golkar Party is scheduled to hold its final campaign in Jakarta on Friday. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar said that for the time being the acceptable level of the currency was at Rp 8,000 to the dollar. \par \par \uc2  "For now, the market values the rupiah at around this level and the government is happy with that," he said. \par \par \uc2  Ginandjar said that the campaign had not caused a negative impact on the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  as the electioneering activities turned out to be non-violent. \par \par \uc2  He pointed out the positive development in key \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators such as inflation, \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  and the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  Inflation in May was negative 0.28 percent, which was the country's third month in a row of deflation. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin expected on Tuesday that inflation this year should be in the range of 10 to 13 percent. \par \par \uc2  The low inflation expectation and the relatively stable rupiah has provided the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  with room to allow domestic \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to decline during the past few months. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  targeted its benchmark interest rate to go down to the 20 percent level by the end of this year. \par \par \uc2  The average interest rate of a \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  one-month SBI promissory note fell to 24.65 percent at Wednesday's auction, compared to 26.12 percent last week. \par \par \uc2  Some analysts, however, warned \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  that a further decline in the interest rate would be detrimental to the rupiah because of the anticipated remaining political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  "An interest rate of 26.12 percent is already near the parity level. And if you continue to push down the rate, the rupiah will weaken," said a market analyst. \par \par \uc2  He said that the country's political landscape would remain unclear over the next several months ahead of the presidential election in November. \par \par \uc2  He added that questions on how the government would secure financing for its costly bank recapitalization program without causing a budgetary strain, and how the government could push bad debtors of domestic banks to repay their nonperforming loans were among the remaining \b \highlight22\uc2 economic uncertainties\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The Indonesian Bank Restructuring Agency and several domestic banks announced on Tuesday their list of debtors in a bid to push them into debt restructuring talks. \par \par \uc2  The bad debtors, particularly at the seven state banks, are mostly well-connected businessmen who had been reluctant to agree to a restructuring agreement because of a strong possibility that they would have to give up a large slice of their businesses to repay their debts. \par \par \uc2  The analyst said the rupiah could weaken because more local corporations would have to purchase dollars following their foreign debt restructuring agreements with creditors. \par \par \uc2  "Debt restructuring also means debt repayment," he added. (rei/prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv63009jn\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
