\par\par \b \uc2  Utilization of export credit guarantee facilities low - BI. \b0\par\par\uc2 830 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 June 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  8 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): The utilization of financing facilities provided by foreign governments and financial institutions for local exporters to import raw materials has been very low due to the volatility of the rupiah and problems in the domestic banking industry, according to \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2 . \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said in its 1998/1999 annual report issued last week that out of the US$3.9 billion in a letter of credit (L/C) provided by overseas institutions, only some $1.1 billion or 26.7 percent was utilized by exporters during the period ending in March. \par \par \uc2  "The utilization of the various L/C guarantee schemes has not been maximal primarily because of the \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the expectation of the exchange rate of the rupiah against the U.S. dollar and the high commercial risk bore by the (local) banks," BI said. \par \par \uc2  BI said that foreign exchange revenue from exports was very important to help finance the country's \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  Indonesian exporters were not able to take advantage of the sharp fall in the rupiah against the U.S. dollar when the currency hit its lowest point last year due to difficulties in importing raw materials as L/Cs opened at local banks were mostly rejected by overseas banks who lost confidence in the local banks. \par \par \uc2  BI said that financial institutions from Japan, the U.S., Canada, Germany, Australia and the United Kingdom subsequently provided the various L/C guarantee schemes after the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  agreed to back them up. \par \par \uc2  But the volatility in the value of the rupiah has created difficulties for the exporters to make business calculations, preventing them from utilizing the L/C guarantee schemes. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, the high non-performing loans (NPLs) and the risk of breaching the legal lending limit ruling has discouraged local banks to engage in L/C business or other lending activities. \par \par \uc2  "After increasing by 7.9 percent in the previous \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year, export value in 1998/1999 dropped by 15.6 percent to $47.4 billion," BI said, adding that in addition to the L/C problem, the low prices of export commodities also contributed to the poorer export performance. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  said non-oil and gas imports plunged by more than 30 percent during the period partly due to the L/C difficulty. \par \par \uc2  The country's export performance remained poor at the start of the 1999/2000 \b \highlight22\uc2 fiscal\b0 \highlight\uc2  year despite efforts by the government to fix the banking system and stabilize the rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) reported last week that total exports in April declined by 3.78 percent to $3.77 billion from $3.92 billion in March, with non-oil and gas exports dropping by 4.40 percent. \par \par \uc2  "Exports of textiles, timber products and electronics dropped significantly," BPS chief Sugito Suwito said referring to the country's major non-oil and gas export products. \par \par \uc2  BPS also said imports in April fell by 7.41 percent to $1.80 billion below the level in March. \par \par \uc2  The government has closed down several banks and has started recapitalization of surviving banks in a bid to restructure the industry and improve the banks' capital condition in order to allow them to start lending activities. \par \par \uc2  The government is also pushing ahead with efforts to restructure the massive NPLs at local banks. \par \par \uc2  BI deputy governor Subarjo Joyosumarto expected local banks could start giving credit in July, but warned that it would also depend on the progress with the debt restructuring process. \par \par \uc2  BI Governor Sjahril Sabirin said that positive progress with the bank recapitalization and NPLs restructuring program as well as a smooth and fair general election would provide stability for the rupiah as confidence that the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  could revive itself. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia is to hold its landmark general election on Monday. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been stabilizing at around Rp 8,000 to the dollar over the past couple of months on the back of improving the macroeconomic picture, particularly in inflation. \par \par \uc2  Minister of Industry and Trade Rahardi Ramelan said last week that the government has established a special financing agency to support export-oriented companies. \par \par \uc2  He said that the agency will be named Bank Ekspor but it will not raise \b \highlight22\uc2 public\b0 \highlight\uc2  funds to finance its activities. \par \par \uc2  BI said in the annual report that export revenue would lessen pressure on the country's balance of payment. \par \par \uc2  BI said although Indonesia enjoyed a net capital inflow of $2.2 billion in 1998/1999, compared to a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of $7.6 billion in the previous period, it was primarily caused by the government's overseas borrowing of $12.5 billion, particularly from the International Monetary Fund. \par \par \uc2  BI pointed out that the net private capital flow was at a \b \highlight22\uc2 deficit\b0 \highlight\uc2  of $10.3 billion as foreign direct investment has plunged. \par \par \uc2  "Instability in the \b \highlight22\uc2 economy\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  in the social and political condition has lessened the interest of foreign investors to make investments," BI said.(rei). \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv67009mt\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
