\par\par \b \uc2  Rupiah could strengthen further - BI. \b0\par\par\uc2 672 \uc2 words\par \uc2 24 June 1999\par \uc2 Jakarta Post\par \uc2 JKPOST\par  1 \par \uc2 English\par \uc2 (c) 1999 The Jakarta Post\par \par \uc2  JAKARTA (JP): \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  Governor Sjahril Sabirin said on Wednesday it was possible for the rupiah to further appreciate to around Rp 6,000 to the U.S. dollar without threatening the country's export competitiveness. \par \par \uc2  "It is good enough if the rupiah can stabilize at the current level of around Rp 6,500. But it is possible for the rupiah to further strengthen to around Rp 6,000," Sjahril told reporters after a meeting with President B.J. Habibie. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah strengthened to the Rp 6,500 level on Wednesday in the mid-day trading session but closed lower at Rp 6,715. \par \par \uc2  He also said that the stronger rupiah would not hurt the country's export competitiveness. \par \par \uc2  He said that based on the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's calculations taking into consideration the real exchange rates of other crisis-hit currencies in the region, exports would remain competitive at an exchange rate of around Rp 6,000 to the dollar. \par \par \uc2  Sjahril said that the rupiah's strong appreciation reflected declining political risks in investing in the country. \par \par \uc2  "In the past there was a political \b \highlight22\uc2 uncertainty\b0 \highlight\uc2  ahead of the elections. Now the general elections are over," he said. \par \par \uc2  Indonesia held landmark elections on June 7, which defied earlier expectations and ran peacefully. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah gained 1.25 percent on Wednesday on Sjahril's comments. \par \par \uc2  The currency continued its strong rally to close at Rp 6,715 to the dollar on Wednesday, compared to Rp 6,800 the previous day. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said Sjahril's comments prompted off-shore banks to buy more rupiah. \par \par \uc2  The \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2 's decision to allow the interest rate of its benchmark one-month SBI promissory note to decline further to 20.34 percent on Wednesday from the previous level of 22.50 percent also did not affect the rupiah. \par \par \b \highlight22\uc2 Bank Indonesia\b0 \highlight\uc2  has been allowing \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to decline without hurting the rupiah on the back of improving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  indicators, particularly inflation. \par \par \uc2  The International Monetary Fund's Asia Pacific director, Hubert Neiss, called on the \b \highlight22\uc2 central bank\b0 \highlight\uc2  on Tuesday to further allow \b \highlight22\uc2 interest rates\b0 \highlight\uc2  to decline to fuel an \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  recovery. \par \par \uc2  The rupiah has been on an upward trend over the past couple of weeks following the country's peaceful election process and improving \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions. \par \par \uc2  A positive remark from visiting IMF first deputy managing director Stanley Fischer on the weekend about the country's political and \b \highlight22\uc2 economic\b0 \highlight\uc2  conditions encouraged investors, sending the rupiah past the crucial Rp 7,000 level at one point on Tuesday. This was the first time for this to happen since early February 1998. \par \par \uc2  Dealers expected the rupiah to consolidate over the coming days, but said the sentiment was still there. \par \par \uc2  Meanwhile, shares dropped 1.4 percent on Wednesday in mixed trade amid selling pressure in some large cap counters. \par \par \uc2  The Jakarta Stock Exchange composite index slid 10.013 points to 700.669 on trading of 1.880 billion shares valued at Rp 1.281 trillion. \par \par \uc2  But gainers outnumbered losers 134 against 46. \par \par \uc2  Shares in state tin mining company Tambang Timah were down Rp 850 to Rp 6,425, while state gold and copper mining firm Aneka Tambang was down Rp 50 to Rp 1,550. \par \par \uc2  State telecommunications firm Telkom was down Rp 100 to Rp 4,700, and Indosat fell Rp 1,075 to Rp 14,150. \par \par \uc2  Cigarette giant Gudang Garam fell Rp 275 to Rp 19,925 while Sampoerna was down Rp 1,100 to Rp 18,500. \par \par \uc2  Indofood suffered heavy selling pressure, sending its stock price on a Rp 975 descent to Rp 10,000. \par \par \uc2  Dealers said the selling frenzy was caused by a report that the Salim Group, Indofood's owner, would further divest its stake in the company by up to 20 percent. Salim needs the cash to repay debts. \par \par \uc2  Banking counters including Bank Internasional Indonesia and Bank Bali gained respectively by Rp 25 to close at Rp 250, and Rp 100 to close at Rp 1,600. (rei/prb) \par \par \uc2  Copyright 1999 The Jakarta Post. \par \par \uc2 Document jkpost0020010906dv6o00a2u\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw298\pich36\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4470\pichgoal540
